notesStmt.note: Folios 13 and 15 are imperfectly preserved. The upper half of folio 14 is damaged.
Only half of folio 83 is preserved.
Several folios are more or less damaged.
There is a gap after folio 86.
Part of folio 104 is torn off.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Fragments of Arabic commentaries on various biblical books and a part of a Hebrew grammar in Arabic.

supportDesc.extent: 111 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). Part I: Folios 1-17 Part II: Folios 18-74 Part III: Folios 75-82 Part IV: Folios 83-95 Part V: Folios 96-111;

layoutDesc.layout: Part I: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15-18; written lines: 15-18; Part II: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15-18; written lines: 15-18; Folio 18r is a title page. Part III: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15-18; written lines: 15-18; The biblical passages are quoted in Hebrew and given in Hebrew script. Part IV: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15-18; written lines: 15-18; Part V: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 18; written lines: 18; Some headings of chapters are given and extant.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Four different Naskhi hands of approximately 11th to 14th century.Part I: A cursive Naskhi hand of the 12 or 13th century.Part II: A cursive Naskhi hand of 12 to 13th century (same as in part I above).Part III: A cursive Naskhi hand and square and semi-cursive Oriental script of 12th to 13th century.Part IV: A Naskhi hand and Hebrew square Oriental script of approximately 14th century.Part V: A Naskhi hand of approximately 11th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Comm. On Pentateuch. Etc. Brit. Mus. Or. 2561.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [112v].
